rComments: Great prof but the topic of 3777 is abstract. It's a tough class (1 essay style exam, 1 research paper, essay style final) but if you really pay attention, it's definitely do-able, just takes more effort than most. He is very knowledgeable and has taken the time to help students and thoroughly answer any questions. He does go on tangents though.

This was the most abstract class I have ever taken (in 5 years of university). It feels like he talks to himself rather than actually teaching any concepts. Exams were 2 questions and based purely on interpretations made in class. Studying actually slides and course content was absolutely useless :-)

Attendance wasn't mandatory, but midterm/final short answer questions were directly addressed only in class, so going to class definitely made studying easier. Nice prof but oftentimes went on tangents, which can be hard to sit through at 8:30. Course material was super dense but he gave lots of hints as to what we would be tested on.

Interesting course. Sylvain's teaching style drifts a lot but you can tell he likes what he does. Labs are repetitive but an easy 10%. I especially liked how he always tells you exactly what to study the lecture before an exam which makes studying so much easier. Exams are fair - 35 MCQs and 2/3 SA for midterms and 65 MCQs and 4 SA for the final

Really nice guy but so hard to listen to during lectures especially at 8:30.. He is goes off on tangents every class and talks about nothing for the majority of the class time. Midterms and exams weren't too bad, definitely read the textbook. Overall an okay prof, think it could be more interesting with another prof
Mandatory class participation and attendance. Interesting subject, terrible teaching. Mid-term is all memorization and is very hard. Hands it back AFTER drop date. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS WITH HIM!

Bonne impression au début, mais plus le cours avance, plus que c'est plate. Il n'est pas intéressant à écouter et ces notes et powerpoint ne font pas de sense. Les examens n'ont presque pas rapport à ce que nous apprenons. À éviter.
Nice guy but I found his lectures very difficult to follow. Vague expectations. Course had too great of a a focus on memorization. The tutorials were easy marks which definitely helped.

He is actually hilarious and has a very dry and subtle sense of humour. Going to lectures can be entertaining but he is slightly tangential and clearly doesn't have full mastery of the English language. Pretty tough evaluations but they're not unfair. You certainly need to have a deep understanding of the concepts to succeed in his course.

This was the most frustrating class I have ever taken in my university career! Worst professor ever! The professors expectations were extremely unclear and he was constantly changing his expectations. His slides made no sense, and not only did they contradict eacother but they also contradicted the textbook! AVOID AT ALL COSTS!
This prof is not interesting at all and the class is so boring. He does nto care for students to pass at all.

I thought this prof was good until he completely screwed everyone over in the midterm. He did not hand in the midterm until after the drop date and gave everyone low grades. He is completely unorganized and dosen't interest me at all.

This teacher is extremely good. He takes time to make you understand what the hell you are doing. He will do everything step by step and tells you why. He would never put 100 formulas in front of you and not care if everyone is completely lost. He is alawsy available to meet with his students. A+

It's not his fault he can't speak English, but he talks very fast, is impatient when asked questions, we had 2 midterms, a final and a paper, and his attitude was that teaching us was not a priority. Terrible prof for an intro to cognition! Lots of work without the motivation. Text was great, but I had to organize a study group to get through this.

urgh the most boring class ever... he just drifts off into explainations that make no sense... attendence AND participation are mandatory... if u have him, make sure you bring a book or laptop to keep busy during the class cuz its total hell

teaches well, interacts with students a lot, tries his best to explain things. Focuses more on the theory in stats then practical which i find is good helps you understand how and why your doing this as opposed to just the how, easy exams but you would still need to attend the class because the text book sucks

Very animated and lively teacher who encourages participation, active thinking, and integration of material.  I learned a lot and enjoyed the class.  Perfect class for extroverts who want to participate.  The lab report, however, was rather challenging.  I enjoyed the class and recommend it for all psych. majors.

Very understanding prof... understands what's going on with his students, very focused on teaching in a manner that suits them. Pleasant class.... really enjoyable to have constant interaction between him and the students as well as students amongst one another. Theory lectures one class and discussion the other was enjoyable! GOOD STUFF :)

The class is fun!!! You learn a lot!  Go for that class! The prof is fun, and he gives you the chance to express your self. Your participation in the class is VERY important, you have to share your experience with the third age people. You won't regret it!

This class was great until he decided to get his TA to teach all of the remaining classes left. His TA was not good at teaching. His TA wrote the final exam too. And made it incoherent. The paper is like writing a thesis on a topic that you have no real understanding about. Do not take this class.
